'''Sergio Marcon''' (born [[9 November]], [[1970]] in [[Cormons]]) is an [[Italy|Italian]] [[Football (soccer)|footballer]]. He plays for [[Calcio Portogruaro-Summaga|Portogruaro]].
==Football career==
Marcon started his career at [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]]. He then played some minor clubs. He followed [[A.S. Andria BAT|Fidelis Andria]] promoted to Serie B in summer 1992.

In summer 1994, he joined [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] of Serie B until November 1994.

Marcon played his second spells for [[A.S. Andria BAT|Fidelis Andria]] in Serie B until summer 1996 the club relegation.

He played for [[Piacenza Calcio|Piacenza]] of Serie A between 1996 until 1999, as backup of [[Massimo Taibi]] and then [[Matteo Sereni]], [[Valerio Fiori]]. He played for [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]] as regular starter in Serie B since summer 1999, and won promotion in summer 2001. He played for [[Ternana Calcio|Ternana]] in another two Serie B seasons.

In summer 2003, he signed for Serie A team [[A.C. Ancona]], where he compete with [[Alessio Scarpi]] and [[Magnus Hedman]]. After the club relegation, he joined [[A.C. ChievoVerona|Chievo]] of Serie A.

In summer 2005, he joined [[Vicenza Calcio|Vicenza]] of Serie B, as backup of [[Giorgio Sterchele]].

